\par 
\par "Aye, Skipper."  Ramsey plugged a monitor phone into one of the board circuits ahead of him, glanced to the telltale above it.  As he did, he noted that the pellet in his neck had almost lost the sound of the tube behind them.  
His hands continued to move the internal pressure ahead of the depth requirement.  The outside pressure repeater above his head showed 2600 pounds to the square inch, still climbing.  
Abruptly, the temperature recorder responded to their entrance into the cold current.
\par 
\par Ramsey spoke into his chest mike:  "We're in the cold, Skipper."
\par 
\par Back came Sparrow's voice:  "We have it here."  Ramsey's pressure repeater climbed through 2815 pounds, steadied.  He felt the deck beneath him come up to level.  Relays clicked, a bank of monitor lights
