Something about Sparrow.  Ramsey's gaze ranged over the board in front of him.  His ears felt tuned for the slightest sound over the monitor phones.  He glanced at the oscilloscope in the right bank:  only background noise.  
For a fleeting instant, Ramsey felt that he was one with the ship, that the instruments around him were but extensions of his senses.  Then it was gone and he could not recapture the feeling.
\par 
\par In the control room, Sparrow fought down the twitching of a cheek muscle.  He replaced a tube in the sonoran system, extracted another, read the code designation from the tube's side:  "PY4X4."
\par 
\par Garcia, beside him, ran a finger down a check list:  "Fifteen ounces plus."
\par 
